section.section:
Except as provided in § 13-110 of the Transportation Article, the Motor Vehicle Administration shall issue a title, free and clear of any lien, to the purchaser of any motor vehicle or mobile home sold under this section, if the holder of the lien on the motor vehicle or mobile home submits to the Motor Vehicle Administration a completed application for a certificate of title with:
A copy of the newspaper publication required by subsection (b) of this section;
A copy of the registered or certified letter required under subsection (b) of this section to be sent to holders of perfected security interests in the motor vehicle or mobile home and the Motor Vehicle Administration, and the return card;
A copy of the registered or certified letters required by subsection (b) of this section to be sent to the owner of the motor vehicle or mobile home, and the return card;
If applicable, a written statement from the lienor that the lienor stored the vehicle in accordance with an agreement with an insurer;
An auctioneer's receipt;
If applicable, certification by holders of perfected security interests;
In the case of mobile homes manufactured after 1976 and motor vehicles, a pencil tracing of the vehicle identification number or a statement certifying the vehicle identification number; and
Any other reasonable information required in accordance with regulations adopted by the Administration.

If the notice required under § 16-203(b) of this subtitle was sent, the proceeds of a sale under this section shall be applied, in the following order, to:
The expenses of giving notice and holding the sale, including reasonable attorney's fees;
Subject to subsection (f) of this section, storage fees of the third party holder;
The amount of the lien claimed exclusive of any storage fees except as provided in subsection (f)(2) of this section;
A purchase money security interest; and
Any remaining secured parties of record who shall divide the remaining balance equally if there are insufficient funds to completely satisfy their respective interests, but not to exceed the amount of a security interest.

Except as provided in paragraph (3) of this subsection, if the notice required under § 16-203(b) of this subtitle was not sent, the proceeds of a sale under this section shall be applied, in the following order, to:
A purchase money security interest;
All additional holders of perfected security interests in the property;
The expenses of giving notice and holding the sale, including reasonable attorney's fees;
Subject to subsection (f) of this section, storage fees of the third party holder;
The amount of the lien claimed exclusive of any storage fees except as provided in subsection (f)(2) of this section;
Any remaining secured parties of record who shall divide the remaining balance equally if there are insufficient funds to completely satisfy their respective interest, but not to exceed the amount of a security interest.
